methods.getAdded:
Fetch the resulting RowSet of added values.

:return: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.RowSet) added RowSet
methods.getModified:
Fetch the resulting RowSet of modified values.

:return: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.RowSet) modified RowSet
methods.getRemoved:
Fetch the resulting RowSet of removed values.

:return: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.RowSet) removed RowSet
methods.validate:
Perform backwards compatible validation checks.

:param update: (io.deephaven.engine.table.TableUpdate) - The update originally passed at construction time, used only for logging debug info on error
:param sourceRowSet: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.TrackingRowSet) - The underlying RowSet that applies to added/removed/modified

text:
Expands TableUpdateListener.onUpdate(TableUpdate)'s Update into a backward compatible ARM (added, removed,
 modified) by expanding keyspace shifts.

 Using this is almost always less efficient than using the Update directly.
